spanGrp.span: I have a very hard life
yas gaw aa qany dayawut ab nawed da nyak qo
Often I often I go until I cry in the rooad, I tell myself
Huwa naenda mpaka nalia barabarani najisemea hivi
If I look, I dont have any children close to me
Nikiangalia sina mtoto wa karibu yangu
Theyve become very far from me
nyas ga gahoonaj uudeeny aa gayeeny ak ni aa gidabani
Often my head, it makes me wonder What is this?
Huwa kichwa changu inawaza kuwa hivi hiki nini
This feeling of hunger the broke out
I dont have anyone to look after me
Even if one person would guide me
This wont end, this problem, I am crying every day
Haitaisha hii shida ambalo nalia kila siku
shideen ni andawiin gwacheed gey gwand orjeedeny quwar gwach mandawiina shiid
This problem which I see, if my boy were home I wouldnt have any problems
Hii shida niliyonayo kama kijana wangu yupo nyumbani nisingekuwa na shida
There is the problem of the children not having clothes
Kuna hili la watoto hawana nguo
Like this and who will look after all of them?
Hivi ni nani atawaangalia hao wote
And am I not a man?
And am I not a man?
To prepare a homestead, it depends on me, Ive become a man
Kutengeneza boma inaniangalia mimi nimekuwa mwanaume
iimich qed qang'ony pangajand daw dalach hiilog
If it becomes another day, I take my machete to go cut trees
lkikucha mimi naahika panga kwenda kukata masanzu
gwacheed gwand quwar dayeegees gwach aa mandn shidayni
My children, if they were at home, I wouldnt have this problem
Watoto wangu wangekiwa nyumbani shida hiki kisingekuwepo
Me, Im a woman, and now Im a man
Mimi ni mwanamke na hapo ni mwanaume
The hunger is harsh, you feel hunger first
Njaa ni kali unaangalia kwanza njaa
aa ging'ul ga shideed quwar qanaha maba
And you look at the problems at home, there is no rest
Na unaangalia shida nyumbani hakuna afadhali
And we give birth to them and they dont listen to us
They dont know the home language
If you tell a child something
gwarung'nanony gid migas ar gurorodang' gwarung'nanony
They tell you something that in your heart you dont want to be told
Anakwambia neno ambalo hata roho yako haikupenda uambiwe
Instead of them speaking our language
They talk a language that isnt yours
Anazungumza lugha ambao siyo ya kwenu
qamn ar da gil ab hiiji
Even if you look at this thing
mandan gidab giqoah aa giyeshi na gida gidaday
Theres nothing, to notify them and tell them "Hey, do you feel what I feel?"
Hakuna kwamba utamshitua na kumwambia hivi unaona ninachoona
If you tell them "Hey, what I feel, do you understand?"
Ukimshitua na kumwambia hivi ninqchoona unaona
niny gong'adanan ng'ashand did megas egushin
They answer with things that cant be said
Now how will we be able to use our language?
diyeed irugs deebug qaqas nyas qwayiiny itang'w gidaba
If you tell the children that it would be nice to listen to you, that
Kitu ukiwaambia watoto ingekuwa heri kukusikiliza kwamba
And you are talking in the home language
Now they have left my ears
ind girugsiin jaft aa kabureed ja gwarung'nanony gidquwari qwayam qut
If you talk with a child, instead of them talking the home language they change their language
Ukiongea na mtoto badala aongee kinyumbani anabadilisha lugha
If they were even here, you feel ashamed
And they have changed the language, they have talked to you in another tribes language
Na amebadilisha lugha amekusema (kwa mkabila mwingine)
aa qang'ulanenyi ar ng'ul aa ginugs qang' qwanal gid rugs
They look at you and if you scowl at them they know what you told them
Anakuangalia na hata ukimkonyeza anajua ulichomwambia
We had a lot of respect
An elder, if you met them
Mzee wa watu hata ukikutana naye
gisis shim diya ar gagur aa gwayeshnoony dab uun siinan giti uuda
You respect them a lot, even if they call you and tell you to go do something, "You, girl"
Unamfanyia heshima sana hata akikuita akakuambia nenda kafanye kitu fulani wewe binti
You will go and do it
A wife, if she sends you
dabo osiinan gitin ar qwenga giwun bid qweng aa giyasi
"If you do this one thing for me," even if it is firewood, you will cut it and give it to them
Mkanifanyie kitu fulani hata kama ni kuni utachuma na kumpelekea
With the respect of the old days
Now we give birth to children who dont listen to us
Its fading a way, the traditional ways arent around any more
Ive struggled, and there isnt anything
You wont explain anything to them about our traditions
gotelnanony gid quwar gwarung'nanony gil nut
They should answer you in our language, they answer with another language
Akujibu kwa lugha yetu anajibu kwa lugha nyingine
ak na iidu giqaweedees na asese
Now how will it help us?
iibalol gidquwari saw gorut gwqrugnan gid emeed suk
If you speak in the home language to them they go out to speak another language
Ukiongea kwa kinyumbani wao wanatoa nje kwa kwa kuongea lugha nyingine
